 instantiate a `FileHandler` with specific constructor arguments. This allows configuring filters and formatters at a more granular level without altering the global config. Overall, it seems simpler and aligns better with the public API.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining config properties**\\n\\nI’m wondering if we should test the configuration properties precisely. The call sites only use filters and formatters through the LogManager, which makes me think that utilizing arguments for file configuration could be more robust. However, it seems that when the line executes, there's a property lookup for the filter and formatter. Maybe I should consider this further to ensure everything runs smoothly without any unexpected issues. It's all about finding the right balance!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying class structure**\\n\\nI’m considering whether public nested classes count as top-level classes, and it seems like they don't. I need to finalize my thoughts on this. However, I might also want to mention that no tests have been run, which could be affecting my conclusions. It's essential to be accurate here, so I’ll work on wrapping up that detail. It’s easy to overlook these nuances, huh?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated active-class test:\n\n- Added `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/src/test/java/tomcat/FileHandlerTest.java`\n\nWhat it covers:\n- Configures `org.apache.juli.FileHandler` through `LogManager` properties with:\n  - a custom `java.util.logging.Filter`\n  - a custom `java.util.logging.Formatter`\n- Instantiates `FileHandler`, which exercises the reflective `loadClass`, `getConstructor`, and `newInstance` paths in `FileHandler.configure(...)`.\n- Publishes a log record and asserts the custom formatter output is written to the configured log file.\n\nAlso preserved the existing connector introspection test coverage for the reporter-requested `Connector.getProperty(\"bindOnInit\")` / `setProperty(\"bindOnInit\", \"false\")` path.\n\nDid not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b28f2681a54fb94016a35626d69288197a9b93616bc92c638\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 278, "output": 958, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30420, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781883483402, "responseId": "resp_0b28f2681a54fb94016a35625c30648197a3810f5680b17d71"}, "toolResults": []}
